The Sci-Bono Discovery Centre is showcasing its Fourth Industrial Revolution Exhibition. This 4IR exhibition is not only intended to bring awareness to visitors about the 4th Industrial Revolution but also instill positive attitudes and willingness to engage in the 4th IR activities. Through the exhibition, some illustrations of several profound technological advancements that are currently under development are being showcased aimed at transforming everyday lives, including robotics, artificial intelligence, autonomous vehicles, smart home devices, wearableâ€™s, mobile payments, and virtual reality. In the video below, Dr More Chakane who is the CEO of the Sci-Bono discovery centre speaks about the exhibition: 